The paper deals with the design of a control scheme for a morphing quadrotor, which involves robotics (cs.RO) and control systems (cs.SY). The authors also propose a compensation scheme based on geometry-awareness, which involves machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
